The paper proposes a new distance metric and consensus clustering procedure for clusterings, which are common topics in machine learning and data science. The use of a Hilbert space-based representation and the focus on spatial distribution suggest a focus on clustering in high-dimensional spaces, which is often studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of soft and hard clusterings, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The mention of spatial distribution and the use of clustering algorithms suggest a potential focus on computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL), where clustering is often used for tasks such as image segmentation or topic modeling.
